.TH "usb_of_get_companion_dev" 9 "usb_of_get_companion_dev" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
usb_of_get_companion_dev \- Find the companion device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct device *" usb_of_get_companion_dev
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the device pointer to find a companion
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Find the companion device from platform bus.

Takes a reference to the returned struct device which needs to be dropped
after use.
.SH "RETURN"
On success, a pointer to the companion device, NULL on failure.
